N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 2 ยง 16.11 - Paid and voided check file

State Regulations

Checks, paid by the bank, shall be maintained in numerical
sequence for each bank account. Where checks are spoiled before issue, a proper
notation shall be made in the appropriate record, and such checks shall be kept
for inspection by the Comptroller. Notes
